title: Louisiana governor runoff candidates focus on Jindal, Obama
text: BATON ROUGE, La. (AP) - As the two men vying to be Louisiana's next governor move into the campaign ahead of a Nov. 21 runoff, they're asking the state's voters to decide who's more unpopular in the state: term-limited Republican Gov. Bobby Jindal or Democratic President Barack Obama. Republican U.S. ... ...
